HEADWORD: Mesoglœa
<hw>Mes`o*gl⟦oe⟧"a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>me`sos</grk> middle + <?/ a glutinous substance.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A thin gelatinous tissue separating the ectoderm
and endoderm in certain coelenterates.</def> --
